step_data.thought: I've successfully applied a filter to find customers with Tax/VAT numbers by using the wildcard '%' which should match any record that has any value in this field. Looking at the current page state, I can see that the filter has been applied as indicated by the 'Active filters: Tax VAT Number: %' text showing in the filter area. However, the results section shows '0 records found' which means there are no customers in the system that have a Tax/VAT number. The table shows a message 'We couldn't find any records.' This confirms that there are no customers with Tax/VAT numbers in the database. I've completed the task of locating all customers with a tax/VAT number - the answer is that there are none. I should report this finding to the user.
